The paper deals with inferring missing edges in multi-relational knowledge graphs, which is a fundamental task in statistical relational learning. This task involves predicting relations on dynamic or previously unseen knowledge graphs, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The use of graph neural networks (GNNs) also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves working with databases (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL) for applications such as question answering and dialogue. Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) in the context of knowledge graph completion.
